Nmap ( network mapper)
Discover the network using Nmap
$nmap 172.18.0.0/16
  Three way handshake based process, SYN > SYN ACK > RST RST stands for RESET flag to avoid connection. This way we can establish if the port is open and then reset to avoid a connection. 
Different scan speed possible:
$ -TX with X for 1 to 5,  5 being the fastest but can miss some open ports 
$ -sU to able UDP scan, UDP scan is longer than TCP scan because do not seek for any connection.

